&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180220/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/w_1280,e_sharpen:60,q_auto/v1770204084/yhuznlzg2jobmd01i57c.png" width="180" height="" style="padding-top: 12px; padding-left: 12px;     line-height: 100%;    "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180220/rss" title="rolandfranke.nl" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Drawing Connections with CSS Anchor Positioning&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A good tutorial that explains the power that anchor positioning unlocks. Roland notes it ‚Äú&lt;em&gt;feels like layout-aware CSS&lt;/em&gt;‚Äù and is ‚Äú&lt;em&gt;especially powerful for UI patterns where relationships matter more than strict placement&lt;/em&gt;‚Äù. There‚Äôs a CodePen demo here to illustrate what‚Äôs¬†possible.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Roland Franke &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180221/rss" title="frontendmasters.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Performance-Optimized Video Embeds with Zero JavaScript&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî ‚Äú&lt;em&gt;What if I told you, you could lazy-load videos on interaction, without any JavaScript, even above the fold, with only native HTML and¬†CSS?&lt;/em&gt;‚Äù&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Stefan Bauer &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180222/rss" title="go.clerk.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Clerk Skills: AI Agents That Know Current Auth Patterns&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Run &lt;code&gt;npx skills add clerk/skills&lt;/code&gt; to teach Cursor, Copilot, or Claude Code current Clerk patterns for sign-in flows and B2B¬†auth.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Clerk &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #997 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180246/rss" title="developer.chrome.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Throttling Individual Network Requests in Chrome DevTools&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Here‚Äôs a look at a new developer tool (in Chrome 145+) to throttle or block specific network requests. This granular control (found in the Request conditions tab) will help improve debugging/testing, particularly sluggishly loading¬†dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Gasperowicz &amp;amp; Pfaffe (Chrome Developers) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180223/rss" title="matuzo.at" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Introduction to the New &amp;lt;&lt;code&gt;geolocation&lt;/code&gt;&amp;gt; Element&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Support &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180224/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;is limited to Chrome for now&lt;/a&gt;, but Manuel takes us on a quick tour of this promising new HTML¬†element.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Manuel Matuzovic &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180225/rss" title="nerdy.dev" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Nice Select&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Some fun experimentation here pushing the &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180226/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;customizable &lt;code&gt;select&lt;/code&gt; element&lt;/a&gt; to its extremes. Watch the attached video to get an idea of what‚Äôs possible ‚Äì &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180227/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;support is limited right now&lt;/a&gt;, but it's really good food for¬†thought!&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Adam Argyle &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180228/rss" title="a11yblog.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;How the Same Content Always Has Multiple Different Versions&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî An interesting accessibility point here looking at the differences the same content can often have. The visuals here really help make the¬†point.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Diana Khalipina &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180230/rss" title="www.smashingmagazine.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Combobox vs. Multiselect vs. Listbox: How To Choose&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Looks at how each is different, what purpose they serve, and choosing the right¬†one.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Vitaly Friedman &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.0em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180231/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-size: 1.0em !important; font-weight: 500 !important;"&gt;Building a Scroll-Revealed WebGL Gallery with GSAP, Three.js, Astro and Barba.js&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A striking visual image reveal effect you can &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180232/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-size: 1.0em !important; font-weight: 500 !important;"&gt;see in this¬†demo.&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="color: #5a5a5a; margin-top: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6em !important;"&gt;Chakib Mazouni&lt;/span&gt; 
  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.0em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180235/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-size: 1.0em !important; font-weight: 500 !important;"&gt;How AI Is Redefining the Way We Find Content&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="color: #5a5a5a; margin-top: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6em !important;"&gt;Alex Edwards&lt;/span&gt; 
  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
